        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-22T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="772" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/12–2248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-22T11:00:00+03:00">December 22, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 22—8:45 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2989. As telegraph and post offices report transmission telegrams and letters
                    Mukden impossible, Embassy is trying to secure report and arrange communications
                    through Foreign Office as suggested Deptel 1358, December 2.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Dairen 31, Nanking 54.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
